      "end": 5.62,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.62,
      "end": 13.38,
      "text": "information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org. Recorded by Lee Dunkleberg, Fort Worth, Texas,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 14.04,
      "end": 21.4,
      "text": "Dunkleberg.com. ASOP's Fables. The Pomming Granite, the Apple Tree, and the Bramble.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 22.38,
      "end": 27.54,
      "text": "A Pomming Granite and an Apple Tree were disputing about the quality of their fruits,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 28.26,
      "end": 34.32,
      "text": "and each claim that its own was the better of the two. High words passed between them and a",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 34.32,
      "end": 41.36,
      "text": "violent quarrel was imminent. When a Bramble impudently poked its head out of a neighboring",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 41.36,
      "end": 48.1,
      "text": "hedge and said, there, that's enough, my friends. Don't let us quarrel.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 49.5,
      "end": 54.24,
      "text": "End of the Pomming Granite, the Apple Tree, and the Bramble.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
